      <Meanings>
        <Meaning id="86735e8a-7154-4166-a5fc-9cd230c94490" type="Noun">
          <Vi>huyết thanh</Vi>
          <En>The clear, yellowish fluid portion of blood in which blood cells are suspended; often used to transfer antibodies or deliver medications.</En>
          <Example>The doctor administered a tetanus antitoxin serum to the patient.</Example>
          <IsArchaic>false</IsArchaic>
          <Situations>
            <Situation id="c2086886-c40e-40de-b7ce-1d4e92a75c6b">
              <Vi>Trong y tế, huyết thanh được tiêm vào cơ thể để cung cấp kháng thể hoặc điều trị bệnh.</Vi>
              <En>In medicine, serum is injected into the body to provide antibodies or treat disease.</En>
            </Situation>
            <Situation id="17f26b84-f9fd-4034-938f-5d859de71bf8">
              <Vi>Huyết thanh được dùng trong xét nghiệm chẩn đoán bệnh truyền nhiễm.</Vi>
              <En>Serum is used in diagnostic tests for infectious diseases.</En>
            </Situation>
          </Situations>
        </Meaning>
